The paper deals with online linear optimization in Hilbert spaces, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on minimax algorithms, which are commonly used in game theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are relevant to the analysis of algorithms and optimization. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Normal approximations, which is a common technique in statistics and probability theory, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
